Re: New Beginnings</span><hr size=1>   Vermifax scurried around on the edge of darkness bordering the light streaming out of the meeting place. His master had ordered him to scout out the area and find out all the information that he could hear. His scaled skin shimmered slightly in the tourch light. Hearing the voices of many people moving towards him; Vermifax Misanthrope quickly started to cover himself in the brush from around him. The people passed and after the footsteps could no longer be heard the pointed teeth clinched into a hard grin. Standing up and shaking off the leaves and dirt from his battle hardened armor, Vermifax popped his knuckles and his neck before walking out onto the worn path. This was proving too easy.<br>
<br>
  &quot;Who goes there?&quot; a stern face peered into the black. Farrio had been out to smoke his pipe in peace when he heard some movement in the brush next to the building. He pulled the branches back to squint into the darkness. &quot;AGGHHHHHH!!!!&quot; the shout came and a thing leapt from the leaves and knocked him over. Screaming Farrio tried to pull his dagger. Still screaming he heard laughter. &quot;Haha! Silence big brother stop screaming or the elders will think that the darkness has come to swallow us up already.&quot; Farrio swore, &quot;Jessica! How many times do I have to tell you to stop following me! You were told to stay back at the house!&quot; Farrio stood back up and straightened his chain mail and adjust the blade at his hip. He stared at the golden eyes of his little sister. She was still laughing slightly and her long braided hair fell over her shoulder; she looked like the two's momma. &quot;Go home and don't let anyone see you. You are not supposed to be out tonight.&quot; Farrio pointed back towards their home. Reluctantly she turned and started to slowly walk back home. Thinking he had enough scare for one night, Farrio composed himself and brushed the leaves from his short hair and walked back into the meeting house.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
