<br>
Cutting through the crowd like a dull knife through granite, Dreyan struggled his way, finally, from the back of the room to the podium, and addressed the sweat-bathed farmers and shopkeeps and the like. His tousled brown hair framed his young face, but his eyes belayed an age and experience that far outweighed his apparent lifespan. The simple brown travelling robes and black hooded cloak he wore made him less likely to be spotted anywhere, and he blended in to the crowd. People started to shout at him when he reached the dais and attempted to speak; vegetables were thrown at him, curses issued, and the uproar grew.<br>
<br>
Pulling back his hood, he revealed a pair of yellowed eyes, positively feline in appearance. He threw back the robes and cloak, showing the sheen of his green pants and leather straps adorning his body, along with a multitude of scars on his arms between those straps; scars that denoted rank among his people. The tattoo of a lion adorned his left hip, and symobls were either tattooed or carved into his chest as scars. The din died down, but did not stop completely, as there were still a few hushed whispers. Holding his hand high, blue light shone forth, coating everything around him with indigo luminescence; the talking stopped, and tranquillity insued.<br>
<br>
The light stopped as abruptly as it started. Dreyan chuckled to himself, and put his robes back on. &quot;Hehehe... Glad you all quieted down with that; I can only do it once.&quot; A few startled snickers and half-hearted laughs ensued. &quot;As you all know, there's something fishy going on across the Balereth.&quot; People agreed in murmurs and blasphemes toward the forest. &quot;Men have gone missing. The treeline is now our only safe border; Drogoth is no longer the peaceful ruler of these grassy planes. This is our battlefield, and preparations must be made if we are to protect our city.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah!&quot; many of the crowd cried in unison.<br>
<br>
&quot;I, myself, would be of little value in this; I suggest you take military matters into your own hands. As for the forests, however...&quot; Dreyan tightened the gauntlets at their straps, and rubbed the mithral knuckles. &quot;I find myself disgusted at the befowlment of Gaea. Let the animals rule, let the trees flourish; it is for this vision of peace that I go to infiltrate whatever stronghold or destroy whatever beast may lurk beyond our borders. I ask now, with open arms and low expectations-&quot;<br>
<br>
Dreyan flipped in the air like a feather, and landed atop the podium with the grace of a cat. Holding a flexing, muscular arm in the air, he shouted, &quot;Who  is  with  me!&quot;  The room stared blankly at him, no one daring to move, lest he call upon them. Sagging a bit, he muttered, &quot;Don't all move at once... Hey, I can sense at least a few shadow-stalkin creatures out there; come to me after the meeting if you wish for the spoils of *this* battle. Anyone? Anyone at all......?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 9:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone? Anyone at all......?</span><hr size=1> As the crowd's silence roared louder than the waves of the ocean, Farrio fought the urge to rush up to the front and follow the stranger. His mind told him to stay back and wait until later, but his heart told him differently. Confused and somewhat nervous, he stayed quiet and in the back.<br>
<br>
Sure that he was in the clear, Vermifax slowly walked towards the building. He had seen two children outside earlier and now they had left. Sure that the perimeter was clear he crept towards the building to see inside and find out how much these people truely knew. He saw a man shouting about some strange things happening, but none of the true plot against these people. Smiling, Vermifax listened to the shouts of a man about a military move. Nonsense! These people could not hold a candle to his great lord of darkness. Snickering to himself he started back down the trail he came from. This would be too easy.<br>
<br>
Farrio slowly walked behind a small line of people going to talk to the man. He was unsure if this was the best idea he ever had. His parents would be angry with him and make him stay, but that was the least of his fears, he was afraid that they would let him. <p>(Dances and dances around in small circles) 
