<br>
Perdita had been killed only a year ago after wondering into the forest. She had been placed under her sister's care, but while her sister prepared dinner, Perdita ran into the forest to play. She did not understand why it was no longer safe to venture into the forest she did when she was younger. Expecting to find a playground of branches and friends in animals, Perdita went skipping into the darkness. No one quiet knows what she found, but they do know they never found her.<br>
<br>
Screams break the calm waves of her mind. Almost on their own her legs jump to a stand. She could almost hear the laughter and feel the comforting eyes as she walked to the man on the podium. Everyone knew what had happened to her sister, everyone was willing to lend a hand here or there to help ease her pain. They could never understand her pain. If they wanted to help they could have stopped her sister from running into the forest. If they wanted to help they could bring her sister back! But it was Zita's fault her sister went into the forest that night... if she only kept better watch she'd still be here... And it was too late to bring her back... It was the looks she got that made her hold her head high. She was fine... She was fine... She was broken.<br>
<br>
She wore the simple cloth pants and tunic that every poor family from her town wore. She was nothing special and it was likely she would not be much help. She was there, however, and would help in anyway possible. Whatever lived in that forest would pay... They would pay for taking Perdita, for taking the only family she had left.<br>
<br>
Extending a hand towards the man, she speaks in a stern voice, she had to be brave otherwise he would think her a joke. <br>
<br>
&quot;My name is Zita. I am with you.&quot; <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 5:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Deeper into the darkness</span><hr size=1>   Farrio was racing home to gather his things. The man had said to collect his things and meet him in the square with the few other recruits. Rehersing how he would sneak into the house to get the things that would go with him, he slowly opened his window.<br>
<br>
  Finally having all his things gathered and his father's sword at his hip he started for the window. &quot;Son, never let the ideas of others take away from your goals and hopes.&quot; The words echoed in his mind. The words his father had said to him before he had tried to enter the forest. Remembering the day Farrio felt renewed in his quest to go out and help. He was almost out the window when he felt a tugging at his leg. Turning with a dagger in his hand, Farrio meet the fierce eyes of his sister. &quot;I'm going with you!&quot; she said with her own bags flung over her shoulder. Sighing, Farrio stepped down from the window and hugged his sister. &quot;Darling, you are too young to go where I am going. There is danger and I don't want you to get hurt.&quot; Farrio tried to plead with her to make her understand. Finding no avail to the situation he finally nodded and lifted her up to the window. &quot;Ok I'll let you go, but you stay with me and don't get into any trouble.&quot; feeling very stupid for letting her find him Farrio followed out the window.<br>
<br>
&quot;Master, the objective was carried out without those stupid people even knowing I was among their ranks.&quot; Snickered Vermifax as he knelt before the throne shadowed in darkness. He peered into the black and only found two burning red eyes shining back at him. He heard the growling laughter coming from his master. &quot;You prove more useful everyday young Vermifax. Keep the work up and you might just find yourself the master of your own land, or dead.&quot; Wincing at the last remark, Vermifax could hear the laughter. &quot;Leave me now, the plotting for the end of those pathetic creatures is slowly forming and I must have full concentration to finish with the enchantments that will lead to their demise. Darkness follow you everywhere.&quot; &quot;Darkness follow you everywhere.&quot; Vermifax muttered as he quickly scurried away. &quot;And may the fog of fear always hide you from the eyes of men.&quot; he muttered as he left the room. <p>(Dances and dances around in small circles) 
