<br>
Great. Two men down and not even past the city walls. Resting under a street light about three blocks from the nearest gate. Drawing a quarterstaff from behind his cloak, Dreyan made a circle on the ground. He sprinkled a bit of white dust from a pouch, and the ring glowed. He grabbed a fistful of the newcomer's shirt and screamed, with fire burning through his green eyes, &quot;WHAT DID YOU DO TO THEM!!&quot; Blue light glowed from his gauntlets. His eyes calmed, visibly, and he let her go. &quot;No. It doesn't matter. Besides, it probably wasn't you. I didn't feel you cast out your power. There's something out there...&quot; His eyes gazed up, past the lamplight, and up to the roofs.<br>
