She snapped out of some kind of trance, and gave her hello as well. Dreyan stopped, and put his mouth close to her ear. In a quiet whisper, he said, &quot;I'm very alert at night; you could say I'm afraid of the dark. I know about the knife deal, but would you mind explaining it to me? I'd hate to accidentally hurt you if you do it again, and I can't feel that it's yo- PLAIN HOPPERS!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
The massive beasts looked like brown, furless rabbits with small heads and big, beady eyes. The ears were always swept back, as they were always hopping along. Great for steaks! The hind legs were about half of their body, and they stood at least a head taller than a normal man. Dreyan ran, laughing joyously, and jumped atop one as it ran past. The herd was making their traditional clicks, but the squeals of surprise from this one while it tryed to buck him off were ear-splitting. He laughed as if it were nothing. &quot;WOOOOO!! Come on, they're harmless! YEEEEEEEEE-HAAAAAH!&quot;<br>
<br>
It took some goading, but Dreyan finally got everyone mounted up; he couldn't tell if they were really enjoying themselves, but he was having the time of his life! &quot;Wooohooo! North, my friends! Guide with your legs, don't pull their ears, and 'all work and no play makes jack a dull boy'!Hahahahahaaa!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uparadisetheheretic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paradise the Heretic</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://Auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/paradise.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Decay</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 12:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/paradise.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: On tha road again..... Yee-HAWW!</span><hr size=1> Sine had woken when the dreams she had been watching suddenly stopped, meaning the party had been woken too.  Sine, a theif and general mischeif maker, had no regular job, had no family to go back to, had nothing to pass the time.  That is why she followed the party.  Always in the shadows, always listening to their thoughts.  Growing up in the forest, she knew it well, and could slip silently through it faster than any of the great cats.  When the party mounted the hoppers she smiled to herself and couldn't help a little giggle...this was going to be fun! <p><b>Sinfuly Yours,<br>Paradise Perdu<br>"Les vrais paradis sont les paradis que'on a perdu."<b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uryvian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 1:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Of the Light-Of the Dark</span><hr size=1> Shocked and somewhat amused Jessica nodded her head. This would be intersting. She might have to kill the kind hearted aywas. Smirking to herself she looked to the sun and saw the bright star flash with red. The sign of blood, a symbol of death and murder. She would have to watch the moon tonight to find if her beloved brother would be with her or if he would also fall on the cutting board.<br>
<br>
Farrio saw his sister's carefree expression change to one that terrified him. That was the same look their other sister had gotten the day before she was killed for black magic. He would have to keep her under his eye and make sure they did not slip with the powers that were given. He slowly started to think that someone has been following them, more then the usual way, but following them in the mind. Thinking he was insane he looked out over the horizan anyways. Casting a small shield of mist to cover the tracks and another one over his sister's mind to protect her from whatever it was plaguing her.<br>
<br>
Vermifax followed this theif with renewed intrest. At first he had thought she must be a street orchin that was merely playing games, but the power emitted from her made him look twice. He had already seen the powers that little pet controled, maybe without fully grasping the significence of it. The brother also had some sort of ability to block out the unwanted attention the two drew by masking the powers or atleast covering it up. He drew up a mental image of his plan. First was to kill that boy so that the power would be unleashed back into nature, making his master stronger, then he would capture that girl, she would cause great damage freely destroying things in her path for vengence. She might forget what side she is really on. It seems Farrio had not, he played his part perfectly. The two children had been plucked at young ages to be given this great task, although the reason might have been forgotten the requirements were not. Farrio and Jessica, perfect for one another. Vermifax laughed again, the irony of it all. Farrio was playing the older brother role just as he had hundreds of years ago, the two pets were perfect. The memories flooded their way back.<br>
<br>
Long ago Vermifax was standing with his brother at the edge of the cliff. They had a bet that the first one to jump would get to have the other's entire collection of army soldiers. The days when the two were innocent and ignorant. Vermifax had been the younger of the two, his older brother Farrio was always stronger willed and better at everything. Smirking, that was not how it ended up. Jessica had always caught Vermifax's eye, but she was always interested in Farrio. Haha what a trick that was played on them. Over the years after Vermifax gave into the master, Farrio grew weaker and weaker, Jessica was no longer protected by him and they took her. Then came his dear brother. the two were then broken and sent out to play like pawns in the big picture. they were given parents and grew up again only as brother and sister instead of husband and wife. Vermifax's cruel idea. Laughing to himself he saw the mist rise and the fire burn. Perfect, this was way too easy. <br>
<br>
Returning to his plans Vermifax had to somehow figure out a way to dispatch this follower. He decided to plant a nightmare into the dreamreaders path and let it destroy her mind. Laughing again, Vermifax stood drew his black blade and start the chant. The day would be long, but the night, longer. <p>(Dances and dances around in small circles) "I am the monkey king" (quickens the dance) "I am the monkey king!" (Falls on his face but keeps moving in a circle) "I AM THE MONEKY KING!"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhopelessromanticakabeginer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>hopeless romantic aka beginer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lady Love</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/25/02 4:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/StormyFate/fullsize/hopeless+icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Of the Light-Of the Dark</span><hr size=1> Lila returned her attention to her fellow travelers, this was the third time she had caught herself, so deep in thought it could be considered a trance, but she couldn’t help herself “what have I gotten myself into” she murmured and caught the youngest child glaring. Lila smiled, the child’s gaze did not divert till her brother said something and her attention turned elsewhere. But there was something more than brotherly love in his eyes, no not just his eyes, this emotion ran deeper his soul his…….heart<br>
<br>
But what she was seeing couldn’t be they, they were family………were they not? And then there was that feeling, of more than one peer of eyes not leaving there backs ever watching yet not daring to come closer and the greatest evil, the one that scared her most the other travelers were mere dolls she could tell but this, this being this force…they would have to face him, destroy him one way or another<br>
<br>
But it wasn’t going to be easy she knew heck most of them didn’t trust her at all not even there “leader” she had nothing AGAIST him no maybe it was his, care free attitude I mean really, an image of him jumping onto one of the hoppers returned , she remembered the “YEEEEEEEEE-HAAAAAH!” most vividly.<br>
<br>
And that child, oh that child the Jessica non of them knew, her “brother” thought he did but non of them really knew the power she contained the possibilities if she were to fall into the hands of the enemy……no, weather her or her brother liked it or not Lila would have to keep an eye on this one, have to train her, have to…..make sure the child was ready, for Lila could tell, Jessica had a great battle ahead of her, greater than they all could ever imagine…<br>
<br>
